git remote remove origin #Unlinks from boilerplate git
Remove-Item -Recurse -Force .git #Removes .git folder, then can re-init below

Initialize and commit
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial backup"

Create an empty GitHub repo (on github.com), then connect and push
git branch -M main
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/YOUR_REPO.git
git push -u origin main